job_description:
Location:
The Hague, the Netherlands

Security Clearance:
NATO Secret

Reference No:
C002648 / The Hague

Introduction: Under the direction of Deputy Chief C2 Centre, the incumbent will provide comprehensive administrative support to the C2 Centre. The incumbent will act as a point of contact for supported team members and deal diplomatically and effectively with a wide variety of issues, including answering enquiries and assisting in the scheduling of the day-to-day business.

Skills, knowledge, experience required:

Higher vocational training in a relevant discipline with 1 years post-related experience. OR
A secondary educational qualification with 3 years post-related experience;
Sound knowledge and experience in the use of Microsoft office automation packages (SharePoint Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Access or other database application), in the use of computerbased tools for maintaining established web pages;
Excellent command of spoken and written English, with a proven ability to communicate effectively orally and in writing;
Ability to take initiative and a flexible approach allowing the incumbent to respond reliably and competently to changing requirements in a demanding environment;
Excellent inter-personal skills and the ability to be responsive and sensitive to both external and internal customers and staff.

Desirable:

Experience with SharePoint at administration level;
Experience with Project Management Tools;
Prior experience of working in an international environment comprising both military and civilian elements;
Knowledge of NATO responsibilities and organization, including ACO and ACT.

Duties/role:

Being the point of contact for Agency's Tasker Tracker. Attending the bi-weekly meetings and maintain the internal C2 Centre Action List. Ensuring timely coordination of taskers within the C2 Centre;
Being responsible for recruitment tracking and on-boarding of new staff members. Participating in recruitment update meetings and maintaining the recruitment tracking data. Coordinating the provision of personal equipment, office space allocation, etc. Assisting with the off-boarding of departing staff;
Acting as the Information and Knowledge Management (IKM) Officer within C2 Centre. Attending monthly IKM meetings, developing and maintaining the C2 collaboration portal according to the Agency guidelines, assigning reference numbers to the official documents and correspondence. Maintaining electronic distribution lists, chat rooms, relevant information about C2 Centre's personnel, etc. Filing of correspondence and documents in accordance with the Agency's procedures and providing assistance in obtaining requested documents from NCI Agency's Central Registry. Picking up and distributing physical mail from the Registry;
Being the point of contact for Performance Management related matters. Preparing the weekly update status reports for management. Liaise with Chief People Office to communicate any changes. Assisting staff members in queries related to Performance Management tools;
Being the point of contact for E-Leave related matters. Preparing update status report when requested. Liaising with Chief People Office to communicate any changes;
Acting as Alternate Training Authority. Processing the Training Requests for C2 Centre staff members according to the NCI Academy guidelines. Being a Point of Contact between the C2 Centre and NCIA Academy and other training providers. Requesting quotes and processing the Purchase Orders in Enterprise Business Application (EBA). Ensuring timely communication between Academy and the C2 Centre;
Assisting in organizing meetings, workshops and conferences in accordance with Agency procedures. Being responsible for the administrative organizational aspects including requesting conference facilities/hotel accommodation, processing approvals/memos/invitations, requesting linguistic services, quotes from caterers and support to participants and access of visitors to NCIA premises. Processing electronic purchase requests into financial control systems as required;
Making arrangements for travel/in-Theatre assignments, including associated NATO Travel Authorization, reserving accommodation where appropriate, submitting security clearances/visit requests, and preparing purchase orders for conference/exhibition fees;
Preparing correspondence, reports, requisitions, purchase orders and other documents often of a complex technical nature, using word processing, spreadsheet and graphics applications, in accordance with the Agency's official document formatting guidelines;
Deputizing for higher grade staff, if required;
Performing other duties as may be required.

